column2: Sunny- calm- .6" of rain 3 days prior to readings
Sunny- calm- 60 degrees- pine and cotton seed pollen on surface
Sunny- calm- 63 degrees pine and cotten seed pollen on surface.  I took another reading the next day because it was so deep on the 11th.
High clouds- calm- looked a little cloudy
5-10 mph wind- no rain for 16 days-  Has been warm and calm forthis period
Last reading of year- Cloudy- a little rain the day before.  SE winds last couple of days.

column1: Dam construction has started.  Lake is 6-7 in. low
Been raining a 1/2 or more per week all summer.  Lake is warm but algae isn't bad
Dam is complete- but lake still a little low.

column2: Lake doesn't look too good for the 4th.
Lake is the worst since we have been here.  Not clearing up.  warm- but pretty green.

column1: not much rain- been warm- lake has been cloudy- ealiest ever I think

column2: Been cool August- water a little clearer. Most of the year it was a little murky. No rain in weeks. Lake a little low.
Sunny 20- clear- First time with new D.O. meter with Dave Blumer
1st ready this year.  Late warm up again this spring.
Blue green algae this year.  Very bad by our palce- boat landing- north side- probably all over along the shoreline.
Blue Green algae on the lake this year.  Took photo's.
cloudy calm- water not bad- 68 degrees
lake is doing really well this summer- clear as its been all summer for a while.  Very nice.
Rained 2.45" on August 19.  Very cloudy water so I took a reading- still not bad.  Lake was really high
First chem sample of 2016.  Cloudy- e wind 10mph.  Air temp 63.5

column1: Very early for the lake to look this green.
Cora helped with reading today- she seemed to enjoy it.

column2: Clear- calm very nice morning for taking readings

column1: Lake has been around 5-6 ft all summer so far.

column2: Lake is still greenish.  We have had good rains all summer but the lake has not cleared up yet
Had some rain lately again- and the lake has cleaned up

column1: PC- calm and warm for September.  67 degrees

column2: Clear as the lake has been all summer.  Calm- PC and warm- 67 degrees

column1: Daryl Braun helped today.  Going musky fishing as this- no fish!

column2: Lake still clear.  Nice fall so far.  Leaves have just started to turn.

column1: Last reading of the year- took boats out.

column2: Cloudy- 65 degrees- s wind 10 .  5 loons- 2 eagles
After the weekend but it still looks pretty good
taking ore reading if fall because I still have the boat in and the water is really clear.
Very clear water.  Late warm up this year.
Clear- wind around 10 mph- 3 loons- 70.  Lake looking good
Clear- wind 5 mph- 70.  Very nice morning.   lake looks clear for end of July.  No sign of algae  this summer yet.  2 loons.
Cloudy- little windy- 10 mph- 71- no loons today.  Lake looks really good for August.  It looks more like June.

64 degrees- PC- calm.  A little late for my first reading.  No wood ducks in the nest this year.  We did have hooded mergansers however.  Many ducks stopped on there way north.  Mallards- redheads- common mergansers- some woodies- geese- and swans.
64 degrees- cloudy- light wind.  3 loons on the lake.  No chicks seen.  Many geese.  Looks like 5 pairs had a hatch.  67 total geese on the lake.  Not sure why the lake is so murky.

The lake was unusually murky this summer so far.  Not sure why.  We have had plenty of rain and that might be a reason.  It doesn't appear to be algae- more brown than green.  Today was a little better than last week so it might be turning around.  Lots of geese still around.  3 loons.
Rick Root helped today.  Still 67 geese on the lake.  3 loons- cannot tell if we had a chick or not.

column1: 70 degrees- clear- a little chop on the water.  SSW wind 5-10 MPH.
I had trouble calibrating the unit for O2 so I am just entering the temp

column2: Lake is looking a little better.  Around 7 feet is pretty good for late August.  Geese are flying.  3 loons still around.
Forgot to mention in the last comments about the storm we had on 8/5/2019.  Reported winds of 70 mph in the area.  Flipped my boat in the lift.  Used a neighbors (Ric Root) boat for this reading.
